story.title: Spiderlings - Episode 6
story.storyDescription: Danny shouldn’t have popped the bump on his cheek! Baby spiders were inside, and now they’re taking control.
story.creator: web-uploader

author.bio: V. Gardner has a black thumb, bringing death and destruction to every plant she tries to grow. To make up for it, she painted her office forest green and pretends she’s in the darkest corner of the woods as she writes.

story.prePaywallNotification: Who’s ringing the doorbell, and can they save Danny from a bug attack?! Keep reading SPIDERLINGS.
story.postPaywallNotification: What did Danny DO?!! The answer will shock you, in SPIDERLINGS.

messages.text: Susan sends a text to Bryan.
How could you be so stupid as to ring the doorbell, Bryan?
Mama’s hungry and you just rang the dinner bell!
I’m not the threat to you.
The cure would have to be administered precisely.
I have no idea what you’re talking about.
Danny just texted me — someone’s at the door.
I’m just turning into your neighborhood now.
There’s a plumber truck parked in front of your house.
Mom’s call to the plumber, Bill, goes unanswered.
My son is home sick and I don’t want him to be overwhelmed.
Listen, lady. I made this appointment with your husband.
He texted me last night. Told me to be here now.
Don’t worry your pretty little head about it.
Now you prob don’t understand this, but let me explain.
It’s costing you a buttload of money.
My son has the flu and needs to rest.
I deal with literal shit on a daily basis.
Point is, I’ll take my chances on your kid’s bug.
Be in and out before you know it.
Moving jerkily, Danny opens the door.
Bill steps inside and speaks to Danny.
It’s awfully dark in here, son.
Danny steps back, body moving like a marionette doll.
Bill scowls in the shadows at Danny. Something stirs at his feet.
Ugh! Looks like you need an exterminator in here, too.
Bill stomps on a spider, squashing it with his heel.
A garbled noise erupts from Danny as his mouth stretches open, wider and wider.
A text comes in from Mom to Danny.
OMG, Mom. What did I do?
Danny, it’s going to be okay.
Whatever it was, it wasn’t your fault.
I was there, sort of, fighting.
He stepped on one of my babies.
I have what I need to help you now.
I’m in a taxi. I’m on my way.
It felt like knives were in my throat.
Blood. There is so much blood.
My mouth is filled with webs, Mom.
That hole in my cheek. It’s gone.
I think I’m losing my mind.
The spiders, they just came out of everywhere.
BECAUSE I FUCKING ATE HIM, MOM
His blood. I drank his blood!
I didn’t want to, but this THING came out of my mouth.
Even though it was still inside my mouth.
I didn’t want to do it, but it made me swallow the blood.
She’s trying to keep you strong.
She’s trying to take care of you.
Are you making fucking excuses for a goddamned spider?
Mopsie. I see Mopsie. What’s left of her.
She’s in a bundle of webs at my feet.
The spiders are working on the plumber.
He’s going all flat, like Mopsie.
They’re like making him a mummy.
Dragging him to the corner behind the couch.
It’s important for a scientist to be precise.
They have webs covering the door now.
Did they know the plumber was coming?
Of course not. I tried to stop him.
How will you come in now?
I’ll figure it out. What else do you see?
I told you that we combined DNA of several arachnid species.
Funnel spiders back into a cave-like space.
When prey is nearby, they shoot out with tremendous force.
The spiders around me, they’re all shaking.
Splitting. Their backs are cracking open.
My throat is closing — I can’t raise my arms.
Legs are poking out of my teeth.
I love you more than anything in this world.
Legs wiggling down into my stomach.
But I have to talk with Mama.
